{"title": "Little Sunbeam", "description": "Peggy, age eight, blind from birth, is the Little Sunbeam in her family.  Following a serious accident in London, she is sent to spend time with Mr. & Mrs. Tiddy in the village of Lower Brimley, Cornwall.  Peggy is much loved there, but by chance she meets Aunt Caroline, the estranged aunt of her mother. Will this little Sunbeam receive what she wants for Christmas when she returns home \u2013 a reconciliation within the family?  This sweet story is written with much Christian sentiment and faith, in a long series of inspirational stories by Eleanora H. Stooke. - Summary by Larry Wilson", "duration": 10136, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "17868", "name": "Eleanora H. Stooke"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/littlesunbeam_2502_librivox/little_sunbeam_2502.jpg", "copyright_year": "1905", "genres": ["Family", "Religion"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Larry Wilson"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Barry Eads"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Jessie Percival"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "I. Knocked Down", "readers": [19584], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/littlesunbeam_2502_librivox/littlesunbeam_01_stooke_64kb.mp3", "duration": 720}, {"section": 2, "title": "II. Concerning Aunt Caroline", "readers": [19720], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/littlesunbeam_2502_librivox/littlesunbeam_02_stooke_64kb.mp3", "duration": 715}, {"section": 3, "title": "III. The Doctor's Prescription", "readers": [19584], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/littlesunbeam_2502_librivox/littlesunbeam_03_stooke_64kb.mp3", "duration": 834}, {"section": 4, "title": "IV. Peggy's First Day At Lower Brimley", "readers": [16097], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/littlesunbeam_2502_librivox/littlesunbeam_04_stooke_64kb.mp3", "duration": 671}, {"section": 5, "title": "V. An Unexpected Visitor", "readers": [1